38static int
39nvkm_control_mthd_pstate_info(struct nvkm_control *ctrl, void *data, u32 size)
40{
41 union {
42 struct nvif_control_pstate_info_v0 v0;
43 } *args = data;
44 struct nvkm_clk *clk = ctrl->device->clk;
45 int ret;
46
47 nvif_ioctl(&ctrl->object, "control pstate info size %d\n", size);
48 if (nvif_unpack(args->v0, 0, 0, false)) {
49 nvif_ioctl(&ctrl->object, "control pstate info vers %d\n",
50 args->v0.version);
51 } else
52 return ret;
53
54 if (clk) {
55 args->v0.count = clk->state_nr;
56 args->v0.ustate_ac = clk->ustate_ac;
57 args->v0.ustate_dc = clk->ustate_dc;
58 args->v0.pwrsrc = clk->pwrsrc;
59 args->v0.pstate = clk->pstate;
60 } else {
61 args->v0.count = 0;
62 args->v0.ustate_ac = NVIF_CONTROL_PSTATE_INFO_V0_USTATE_DISABLE;
63 args->v0.ustate_dc = NVIF_CONTROL_PSTATE_INFO_V0_USTATE_DISABLE;
64 args->v0.pwrsrc = -ENOSYS;
65 args->v0.pstate = NVIF_CONTROL_PSTATE_INFO_V0_PSTATE_UNKNOWN;
66 }
67
68 return 0;
69}
70
71static int
72nvkm_control_mthd_pstate_attr(struct nvkm_control *ctrl, void *data, u32 size)
73{
74 union {
75 struct nvif_control_pstate_attr_v0 v0;
76 } *args = data;
77 struct nvkm_clk *clk = ctrl->device->clk;
78 const struct nvkm_domain *domain;
79 struct nvkm_pstate *pstate;
80 struct nvkm_cstate *cstate;
81 int i = 0, j = -1;
82 u32 lo, hi;
83 int ret;
84
85 nvif_ioctl(&ctrl->object, "control pstate attr size %d\n", size);
86 if (nvif_unpack(args->v0, 0, 0, false)) {
87 nvif_ioctl(&ctrl->object,
88 "control pstate attr vers %d state %d index %d\n",
89 args->v0.version, args->v0.state, args->v0.index);
90 if (!clk)
91 return -ENODEV;
92 if (args->v0.state < NVIF_CONTROL_PSTATE_ATTR_V0_STATE_CURRENT)
93 return -EINVAL;
94 if (args->v0.state >= clk->state_nr)
95 return -EINVAL;
96 } else
97 return ret;
98 domain = clk->domains;
99
100 while (domain->name != nv_clk_src_max) {
101 if (domain->mname && ++j == args->v0.index)
102 break;
103 domain++;
104 }
105
106 if (domain->name == nv_clk_src_max)
107 return -EINVAL;
108
109 if (args->v0.state != NVIF_CONTROL_PSTATE_ATTR_V0_STATE_CURRENT) {
110 list_for_each_entry(pstate, &clk->states, head) {
111 if (i++ == args->v0.state)
112 break;
113 }
114
115 lo = pstate->base.domain[domain->name];
116 hi = lo;
117 list_for_each_entry(cstate, &pstate->list, head) {
118 lo = min(lo, cstate->domain[domain->name]);
119 hi = max(hi, cstate->domain[domain->name]);
120 }
121
122 args->v0.state = pstate->pstate;
123 } else {
124 lo = max(nvkm_clk_read(clk, domain->name), 0);
125 hi = lo;
126 }
127
128 snprintf(args->v0.name, sizeof(args->v0.name), "%s", domain->mname);
129 snprintf(args->v0.unit, sizeof(args->v0.unit), "MHz");
130 args->v0.min = lo / domain->mdiv;
131 args->v0.max = hi / domain->mdiv;
132
133 args->v0.index = 0;
134 while ((++domain)->name != nv_clk_src_max) {
135 if (domain->mname) {
136 args->v0.index = ++j;
137 break;
138 }
139 }
140
141 return 0;
142}

144static int
145nvkm_control_mthd_pstate_user(struct nvkm_control *ctrl, void *data, u32 size)
146{
147 union {
148 struct nvif_control_pstate_user_v0 v0;
149 } *args = data;
150 struct nvkm_clk *clk = ctrl->device->clk;
151 int ret;
152
153 nvif_ioctl(&ctrl->object, "control pstate user size %d\n", size);
154 if (nvif_unpack(args->v0, 0, 0, false)) {
155 nvif_ioctl(&ctrl->object,
156 "control pstate user vers %d ustate %d pwrsrc %d\n",
157 args->v0.version, args->v0.ustate, args->v0.pwrsrc);
158 if (!clk)
159 return -ENODEV;
160 } else
161 return ret;
162
163 if (args->v0.pwrsrc >= 0) {
164 ret |= nvkm_clk_ustate(clk, args->v0.ustate, args->v0.pwrsrc);
165 } else {
166 ret |= nvkm_clk_ustate(clk, args->v0.ustate, 0);
167 ret |= nvkm_clk_ustate(clk, args->v0.ustate, 1);
168 }
169
170 return ret;
171}
172
173static int
174nvkm_control_mthd(struct nvkm_object *object, u32 mthd, void *data, u32 size)
175{
176 struct nvkm_control *ctrl = nvkm_control(object);
177 switch (mthd) {
178 case NVIF_CONTROL_PSTATE_INFO:
179 return nvkm_control_mthd_pstate_info(ctrl, data, size);
180 case NVIF_CONTROL_PSTATE_ATTR:
181 return nvkm_control_mthd_pstate_attr(ctrl, data, size);
182 case NVIF_CONTROL_PSTATE_USER:
183 return nvkm_control_mthd_pstate_user(ctrl, data, size);
184 default:
185 break;
186 }
187 return -EINVAL;
188}
189
190static const struct nvkm_object_func
191nvkm_control = {
192 .mthd = nvkm_control_mthd,
193};
194
195static int
196nvkm_control_new(struct nvkm_device *device, const struct nvkm_oclass *oclass,
197 void *data, u32 size, struct nvkm_object **pobject)
198{
199 struct nvkm_control *ctrl;
200
201 if (!(ctrl = kzalloc(sizeof(*ctrl), GFP_KERNEL)))
202 return -ENOMEM;
203 *pobject = &ctrl->object;
204 ctrl->device = device;
205
206 nvkm_object_ctor(&nvkm_control, oclass, &ctrl->object);
207 return 0;
208}
209
210const struct nvkm_device_oclass
211nvkm_control_oclass = {
212 .base.oclass = NVIF_IOCTL_NEW_V0_CONTROL,
213 .base.minver = -1,
214 .base.maxver = -1,
215 .ctor = nvkm_control_new,
216};
